    "Create a result type for return evaluation that indicates eligible/not eligible and includes a non-empty reason when not eligible.",
    "Design an abstract return policy base class that defines a public method for evaluating eligibility and includes at least one abstract (or virtual) method that derived policies override to implement policy-specific checks.",
    "Implement at least two derived policies (e.g., Digital policy that always rejects, and Physical policy that checks a return window based on days since purchase). Add an additional stricter behavior for clearance items (e.g., shorter window or always reject) in one of the policies.",
    "Implement a policy selector/factory that chooses which policy instance to use based on the purchased line item. To demonstrate static vs instance members: keep a static mapping/registry of item-type-to-policy-creator (or supported policy keys) while the actual policy evaluation happens on instance policy objects.",
    "Ensure that the code calling the policy uses the abstract base type, not concrete policy types, so polymorphism is required to get the correct behavior.",
