  "scenario": {
    "story": "eShopOnWeb uses a cookie to track an anonymous buyer id for the basket. Several parts of the app read this cookie and assume it is a valid GUID. Support has seen cases where the cookie is corrupted (manually edited, bad client, old data), causing inconsistent behavior. The team wants a single, centralized place to sanitize the cookie for all web requests.",
    "requirement": "Implement ONE feature in the Web project: create middleware that checks the anonymous basket cookie on each request. If the cookie exists but is not a valid GUID, the middleware must delete it from the response and ensure downstream code does not treat it as a valid anonymous id. The middleware must be registered in the request pipeline so it runs before pages/components that read the basket cookie. The middleware must also log when it deletes an invalid cookie."
