{
  "task_name": "Shipping Quote Provider Factory: Create Region-Specific Quote Providers Without Exposing Construction Logic",
  "skill_category": "Design Patterns & SOLID",
  "scenario": {
    "story": "The store needs to show a shipping quote during checkout. In the reference e-commerce app, shipping cost and order totals are computed as part of the checkout flow and can vary by destination. The business now wants to support multiple region-specific shipping rules (for example: domestic flat rate, international base + per-item fee). The team wants a small feature where the shipping quote logic is selected based on destination region, and new regions can be added later without changing existing quote calculation code.",
    "requirement": "Implement ONE feature: a shipping quote service that returns a shipping cost for a checkout draft (destination region + line items). Quote calculation must be implemented by region-specific provider classes (interchangeable behind a shared abstraction). A factory must create/select the correct provider based on destination region without exposing instantiation logic to the caller. The service must validate input and throw a custom exception for unsupported regions. Keep the solution medium-sized (40–150 lines) using multiple classes and methods."
  },
  "targeted_objectives": [3, 5, 8],
  "additional_skills_required": [
    {
      "skill_name": "OOP (Object-Oriented Programming)",
