    "Define a shipping quote result model containing at least the computed shipping cost (and optionally the region used).",
    "Create a shipping quote provider abstraction that can compute a shipping cost given the checkout draft input.",
    "Implement at least two region-specific provider classes with different deterministic pricing rules (e.g., flat rate for one region and base + per-item fee for another). Keep the rules simple and purely in-memory.",
    "Implement a factory component responsible for selecting/creating the correct provider based on the destination region. The service that requests quotes must not instantiate provider classes directly.",
    "Implement a shipping quote service that uses the factory to obtain a provider, validates basic input (e.g., non-empty region, at least one line with positive quantity), and returns the quote result.",
    "If the destination region is not supported by the factory/providers, throw a custom exception type that clearly identifies the region value.",
