      "related_learning_objective": 0
    },
    {
      "criterion": "When updating list id 5 in workspace 10, proposing a title that normalizes to the current list’s own stored title is accepted (does not fail uniqueness).",
      "related_learning_objective": 0
    },
    {
      "criterion": "All repository and validator operations for uniqueness checking are asynchronous (return Task / Task<T>) and are awaited (no .Result or .Wait usage).",
      "related_learning_objective": 0
    }
  ],
  "hints": [
    "Model the problem as: “normalize proposed title” + “compare against normalized existing titles in same workspace”.",
    "Keep the repository interface minimal; only expose what the validator truly needs for uniqueness checks.",
    "If you’re unsure whether to normalize in the repository or validator, prefer a separate normalizer abstraction and call it consistently.",
    "Implement one normalizer that only trims + lowercases, and another that also compresses internal whitespace; switch them in tests to prove the design is interchangeable.",
    "For update scenarios, pass the current list id into the validator so it can exclude that record from the uniqueness query.",
