    },
    {
      "criterion": "For a percentage-based coupon with a minimum-subtotal condition, when the basket subtotal meets or exceeds the minimum, the discount amount equals subtotal * percentage (rounded to 2 decimals if using decimal arithmetic).",
      "related_learning_objective": 0
    },
    {
      "criterion": "For a fixed-amount coupon, the discount amount never exceeds the basket subtotal (final total is never negative).",
      "related_learning_objective": 0
    }
  ],
  "hints": [
    "Start by modeling the basket subtotal calculation without any coupons, using a basket class that contains item objects.",
    "Introduce a small result type to return both the discount amount and the final total, so tests can assert outcomes easily.",
    "Use an abstract base class for coupon rules to share the coupon code and a common method signature for computing discounts.",
    "Create two concrete rule types with different logic and override the calculation method in each one.",
    "In the engine, store rules as the base abstract type and select the matching one by coupon code; then call the overridden method to compute the discount."
