    "Design an abstract base class representing a shipping rule. It should define a method for determining whether the rule applies to a given request, and a method for calculating the shipping cost details.",
    "Implement at least two derived shipping rule types (for example: a flat-rate rule for one zone, and a weight-tier rule for another zone). Each derived class must override at least one base class method so the calculator can use polymorphism.",
    "Create a shipping calculator class that holds a list of rules and uses LINQ to: (1) filter applicable rules, (2) compute candidate costs, and (3) select the best rule (e.g., the lowest final cost).",
    "Add express delivery behavior: if express is selected, apply an extra surcharge (either as a percentage or fixed amount). Decide whether surcharge is handled by the calculator or by the rule implementations, but keep it consistent.",
